article_title: Uninsured in Ohio down to 11% under Obamacare
article_text:

article_metadata.description: Eleven percent of Ohio adults younger than 65 lacked health coverage this year, a sharp drop from 17 percent last year and the lowest rate since the Ohio Health Issues Poll began in 2006. But it’s still unclear how much of the credit for that change goes to an improving economy and how much goes to the Affordable Care Act.
